          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The detector setup consisted of eight, 1 mm",
                "thick silicon detectors of 5*5 cm**2 area placed around",
                "the beam axis:  they formed a 14 cm long parallelepiped",
                "in the target chamber.  Each detector was shielded by a",
                "25 mu-meters thick nickel foil in order to stop the",
                "He-4 ejectiles, the elastic scattering products, and",
                "the light induced by the beam."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A NE102A plastic scintillator, 1*1 m**2, 3.5 cm",
                "thickness, was placed below the target chamber and used",
                "to veto cosmic-ray-induced events in the detectors.",
                "Dead time effects in the detectors were monitored using",
                "a pulser and were kept below 3%. The detector",
                "efficiency in the setup was calculated with a",
                "MONTE-CARLO simulation."
              ]
            }
          ],
